# Project Workflow

## Overview

This task outlines the complete development workflow of the **A Comprehensive Measure of Well-Being (HDI Prediction System)**. The project is divided into eight epics, covering environment setup, data preprocessing, machine learning model development, evaluation, model saving, and Flask web application deployment.

---

## Workflow Phases

### Epic 1
- Environment Setup
- Package Installation
- Project Folder Structure

### Epic 2
- Import Required Libraries

### Epic 3
- Dataset Download
- Dataset Understanding
- Data Visualization

### Epic 4
- Data Preprocessing
- Feature Selection
- Null Value Handling
- Label Encoding

### Epic 5
- Train-Test Split

### Epic 6
- Linear Regression Model Training
- Prediction
- Model Evaluation

### Epic 7
- Save Trained Model using Pickle

### Epic 8
- Flask Backend Development
- HTML Interface
- Application Testing

---

## Workflow Diagram

```
Environment Setup
      ↓
Import Libraries
      ↓
Dataset Collection
      ↓
Data Understanding
      ↓
Visualization
      ↓
Preprocessing
      ↓
Train-Test Split
      ↓
Linear Regression
      ↓
Prediction
      ↓
Evaluation
      ↓
Save Model
      ↓
Flask Deployment
```

---

## Outcome

Successfully established a structured workflow covering every stage of the machine learning lifecycle, ensuring organized development and deployment of the HDI Prediction System.

---

## Result

The workflow serves as a roadmap for implementing the project efficiently while maintaining scalability, code organization, and reproducibility.
